    "In the scope of centralized learning, there have been several works on data management [107,108], wherein a singular party exercises complete control over the entirety of the data.Switching from centralized learning to federated learning, new challenges arise since no single party possesses access to the full dataset; instead, data is distributed across a multitude of clients, each holding only a fraction of the total data.",
